</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>SCR154:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="SCR154"/><meta name="dc:title" content="SCR &#xA;              154-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Senate Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 154</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 77</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to Green Star Veterans and Families Day. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">May 29, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SCR 154, Umberg.
                          Green Star Veterans and Families Day.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would designate May 4, 2026, as Green Star Veterans and Families Day.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_BC682C9E-2E1E-469F-BFF4-5DD8B254EEB7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Veterans of the United States Armed Forces served our country with honor, courage, and unwavering commitment to protecting our freedoms and securing our national defense; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_73C705FF-E0B5-402A-B7BF-3A0C81699C90"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Many veterans who have bravely served continue to face significant mental health challenges upon returning home, including invisible wounds that can profoundly impact their daily lives; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_08ACDC47-6F90-4F6F-B9FD-2B4937EABA4B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Mental health conditions, including post-traumatic stress disorder, depression, and traumatic brain injury, often intensify over time and, without adequate support, can increase the risk of suicide; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_BFB50DAE-B917-4CE9-A253-6AD89BC757D2"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, An estimated 22 veterans are tragically lost to suicide every day, 6,407 veterans took their lives in 2022, and over 140,000 veterans have died by suicide since September 11, 2001; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_931EE180-BD86-4449-B597-38CAE7962F4A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Despite these alarming numbers, Green Star Veterans, veterans who have lost their lives to suicide in connection with their military service, are not formally recognized in our state; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_C42AEB95-9AAD-4F2F-847B-17ADEA7B23AA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Every veteran whose life ends as a result of their service deserves to be honored with the same dignity; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_703CF940-EDA3-4F4A-AF9C-ECDB3AA9B1C2"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The families of veterans lost to suicide deserve the assurance that their loved ones’ service, sacrifice, and memory will be respectfully preserved and recognized; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_26AEF719-5421-47D7-BE83-791BB943DC11"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Green Star Families serve an essential role in sharing their loved ones’ stories, spreading public awareness of the toll service-related mental health challenges have on a veteran, and advocating for stronger prevention and support initiatives to protect future veterans and their families; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_05EAE22B-54D6-47E8-9433-D217B253985D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Green Star Service Banner serves as a symbol to honor our veterans who have lost their lives to suicide in connection with their military service and should be recognized in our state; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_783A0477-0301-4BD8-8ADA-AD79459CFDA3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Senate of the State of California, the Assembly thereof concurring, That the Legislature designates May 4, 2026, as “Green Star Veterans and Families Day” in California; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_EC0D44D6-C274-44A1-B5EC-97873D5FEB4F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature officially recognizes the Green Star Service Banner; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_894EC1C4-15AC-41EC-B0C3-413E4E2790A1"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature honors veterans whose lives were lost to suicide to recognize the resilience and dedication of the families they leave behind and to raise awareness of the ongoing mental health and suicide crisis affecting those who have served; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_89E37020-3F4D-4C23-9EC0-D6CDAD57E679"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Secretary of the Senate transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
